I assume that by status you mean number of confirmations?

Usually a transaction can safely be regarded as 'successful' if it has 3 confirmations or more. The tx object in this api client does not have a field containing the number of confirmations, but you can look at the height of the block containing the transaction:

```php
$latest_block_height = $Blockchain->Explorer->getLatestBlock()->height;
$tx_height = $Blockchain->Explorer->getTransaction($hash).block_height;
$num_of_confirmations = $latest_block_height - $tx_height + 1;
```

