with the two addresses you provided, I get peak memory uses of ~31MiB and ~9.8MiB respectively.

Raising `memory_limit` to 50MiB should be enough to process these addresses. 

I would recommend you to use the pagination provided by `$Blockchain->Explorer->getAddress($address, $limit, $offset)` to lower the memory usage of your script. It enables fetching transactions by packets of `$limit` transactions starting at the `$offset` nth transaction.

$limit = 50;
$offset = 1;
$address = "1A1zP1eP5QGefi2DMPTfTL5SLmv7DivfNa";
$address_info = $Blockchain->Explorer->getAddress($address, $limit, $offset);
echo $address_info->transactions[1]->version;

Substitute the below php code for /src/Blockchain.php
You should need a blockchain api-code because almost IP addresses in Tor network may be blocked due to the request limitation.

```
<?php
/* vim: set expandtab tabstop=4 shiftwidth=4 softtabstop=4: */

/**
 * Short File Description
 *
 * PHP version 5
